<div id="Idea_4097"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4097-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4097">More Consice Rules for the User&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9645-4049">editor</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">It would be helpful to have a one stop set of easily understood rules on FOIA requests and courses of action when those rules fail.  For example, when you submit a request via (e-FOIA) and the agency refuses to acknowledge your request, and after repeated attempts refuses to give you a tracking number; what next?<br/><br/>The U.S. Coast Guard in particular has been very hard to work with on FOIA requests.  They have several hot topic issues inside the agency that they apparently rather not address.<br/><br/>An "If Then" tree on the site would be nice.  "If" Coast Guard does not respond with a tracking number, "then" do this...</div>
